    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.001F85/9</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Emperor</gloss> to the <gloss type="to"
                            >President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin, via Sayville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With deepest sorrow I hasten to inform Your Excellency that my beloved
                    grand-uncle, His Imperial and Royal Majesty, Francis Joseph Roemisch I, expired
                    last night after a short illness. I feel confident that Your Excellency and the
                    American nation will sympathize with the great loss that Austria-Hungary has
                    sustained by the death of His Majesty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
